Opinion:  This is excellent, short and bittersweet. A prefect balance of humor, interest and wholesome sadness. A small gripe would be the semi-lackluster conprocs (but in the end sometimes the basics is all you really need). I also think the photos produced would be given a designation (-1, -A), especially since they are contained separately. Aside for the minor nitpick this is a nearly perfect piece and definitely one of my favorite articles to come out recently. To compound that, it was written as a  which in and of itself is impressive. Easy +1.







